You are implementing the Stage 2 Script Editor panel (`components/stages/Stage2ScriptEditor.tsx`) for a video production pipeline editor. This client component provides a split-pane CodeMirror 6 editor with structured preview and TTS script generation trigger.

Requirements
1. Props: `onAdvance: () => void`.
2. Left pane: CodeMirror 6 editor with Markdown syntax highlighting. Loads script from `GET /api/project/script`. Auto-saves via `PUT /api/project/script` on 1s debounce.
3. Right pane: structured preview re-rendered on 200ms debounce. `NARRATOR:` blocks ŌåÆ blue `Ō¢Ā` prefix. `[VISUAL:]` blocks ŌåÆ teal `Ō¢Ż` prefix. `##` headers ŌåÆ gray section label.
4. Resizable split pane: draggable vertical divider. Persists ratio in `localStorage`.
5. [Generate TTS Script ŌåÆ] button: enabled only when Ōēź1 `NARRATOR:` block is detected. POSTs to `/api/pipeline/tts-script/run`. On success, calls `onAdvance()`.
6. `'use client'` directive.
7. Show `SseLogPanel` with returned `jobId` after triggering TTS script generation.

