Instructions
- CodeMirror setup: `import { EditorView } from '@codemirror/view'`; `import { markdown } from '@codemirror/lang-markdown'`; use `useRef<EditorView | null>` and mount with `new EditorView({ extensions: [markdown(), ...], parent: containerRef.current })`.
- Debounce auto-save: `useEffect` with `setTimeout(save, 1000); return () => clearTimeout(id)` on content changes.
- Structured preview parser: regex-based line scanner: `/^NARRATOR:/` ŌåÆ blue block, `/^\[VISUAL:/` ŌåÆ teal block, `/^## /` ŌåÆ section header.
- Resizable divider: track mouse drag with `onMouseDown` on the divider element; update split ratio state.
- `localStorage` key for split ratio: `'script-editor-split-ratio'`.
- NARRATOR detection: `/NARRATOR:/m.test(content)` to enable the generate button.
- Load script on mount: `useEffect(() => { fetch('/api/project/script').then(r => r.json()).then(d => setContent(d.content)) }, [])`.
- CodeMirror controlled update: call `view.dispatch(view.state.update({ changes: { from: 0, to: view.state.doc.length, insert: newContent } }))` when content loads.

Deliverable
- `components/stages/Stage2ScriptEditor.tsx` ŌĆö split-pane script editor with structured preview and TTS trigger.

